27
00:04:22,220 --> 00:04:24,640
 Yangwu is a secondhand book trading website. 

28
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:27,990
This concept was born out of a book exchange event I did in high school.

29
00:04:27,990 --> 00:04:35,160
That long-ago event proved the simplicity and sincerity of human feelings.

30
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:36,940
But when we enter society,

31
00:04:36,940 --> 00:04:40,810
in this multi-dimensional world of convenient transport and communication,

32
00:04:40,810 --> 00:04:45,300
we find that the distance between people is getting further and further away.

33
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:48,150
I've always believed that people are not isolated islands.

34
00:04:48,150 --> 00:04:52,230
We spend our lives searching for a family to snuggle with, to warm up to,

35
00:04:52,230 --> 00:04:54,590
as well as companions to reflect our souls.

36
00:04:54,590 --> 00:04:56,620
They are the stars of the night sky,

37
00:04:56,620 --> 00:05:01,420
 the lighthouse of the sea, and the everlasting sun. 

38
00:05:02,366 --> 00:05:06,810
 They are the proof that we are alive, and the meaning of our existence. 

39
00:05:06,810 --> 00:05:13,640
 It's when we start to burn for each other that the world becomes so bright and colorful. 

40
00:05:13,640 --> 00:05:16,838
Therefore, a book is not just a book. 
    

41
00:05:16,838 --> 00:05:20,260
It's the means of communication between people.

42
00:05:20,260 --> 00:05:22,050
It is a shelter for the lonely,

43
00:05:22,050 --> 00:05:27,260
a haven for the wandering, a home where warm lights are always on,

44
00:05:27,260 --> 00:05:30,688
and the door is open for the return of the wanderer.

45
00:05:41,180 --> 00:05:44,820
Fu Ying, I don't need this anymore. Keep it.

46
00:05:46,030 --> 00:05:47,710
You...

47
00:05:50,450 --> 00:05:54,111
How is it? Did you get the results from the meeting?

48
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:02,720
What are you doing?

49
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:06,260
I'm moving to the 10th floor.

50
00:06:06,260 --> 00:06:07,960
To the 10th floor?

51
00:06:07,960 --> 00:06:10,180
So our plan is approved?

52
00:06:10,180 --> 00:06:15,577
To be precise, she'll go to the 10th floor, and I'll go to the ground floor.

53
00:06:15,577 --> 00:06:17,130
What are you doing on the ground floor?

54
00:06:17,130 --> 00:06:19,500
Take a cab and go home.

55
00:06:20,150 --> 00:06:24,420
The plan didn't get approved.

56
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:32,659
You don't have to blame yourself.

57
00:06:32,659 --> 00:06:34,840
It's not our fault that the plan didn't get approved.

58
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:37,500
A long time ago, I wanted to tell you.

59
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:41,340
No matter how well our plan is done, it will still be rejected by the company.

60
00:06:41,340 --> 00:06:43,482
Huan Dao is a very mature organization.

61
00:06:43,482 --> 00:06:45,610
Every project that is incorporated into the company's territory

62
00:06:45,610 --> 00:06:46,980
and every piece of content that is produced

63
00:06:46,980 --> 00:06:49,500
is closely related to the company's future development.

64
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:53,511
It's never going to shift at the will of some of us newcomers to the company.

65
00:06:54,550 --> 00:07:00,080
So, they've been making us waste our time from the beginning?

66
00:07:00,620 --> 00:07:03,633
The company already gave us a one percent chance.

67
00:07:03,633 --> 00:07:05,860
It's just that we're all ordinary people.

68
00:07:05,860 --> 00:07:09,788
And miracles don't always happen to ordinary people.

69
00:07:10,450 --> 00:07:13,010
I still don't quite get it.

70
00:07:13,010 --> 00:07:16,060
- And you... 
 - Want to ask me why I got to stay?

71
00:07:16,060 --> 00:07:17,810
And why I got a promotion?

72
00:07:17,810 --> 00:07:21,455
Well, actually, I got an offer letter from headquarters before you got here.

73
00:07:21,455 --> 00:07:24,577
I was offered the position of department manager.

74
00:07:26,180 --> 00:07:29,470
So, Fu Ying, you're the spy.

75
00:07:29,470 --> 00:07:31,010
You're such a good actress.

76
00:07:31,010 --> 00:07:36,320
But I don't understand why you've been working hard with us for a month,

77
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:38,950
doing this for nothing.

78
00:07:39,790 --> 00:07:41,180
I have no idea.

79
00:07:41,180 --> 00:07:43,380
Maybe I was still harboring illusions.

80
00:07:43,380 --> 00:07:46,420
That we're the one percent that can survive.

81
00:07:46,420 --> 00:07:48,080
It's not for nothing.

82
00:07:48,080 --> 00:07:55,130
I was just trying to pull off one last silly romance with my companions.

83
00:08:04,230 --> 00:08:05,840
Fu Ying,

84
00:08:08,380 --> 00:08:10,020
thank you.

85
00:08:18,810 --> 00:08:20,710
What about you?

86
00:08:20,710 --> 00:08:23,960
Do you want to fight again to stay?

87
00:08:23,960 --> 00:08:27,303
Xi Chi, I'm sorry.

88
00:08:27,303 --> 00:08:29,600
It's impossible for me to stay.

89
00:08:30,420 --> 00:08:32,080
Why?

90
00:08:33,310 --> 00:08:37,240
 To sum up, in the future, Yangwu will not only be able to trade secondhand books, 

91
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:39,718
 but will also be able to build a community based on interests 

92
00:08:39,718 --> 00:08:42,190
 and meet more like-minded people. 

93
00:08:42,190 --> 00:08:45,820
 After all this time, this is what you've come up with? 

94
00:08:45,820 --> 00:08:48,205
 Huan Dao is not a charity organization. 

95
00:08:48,205 --> 00:08:53,574
 According to your plan, we need to invest a lot of time and manpower to manage the website. 

96
00:08:53,574 --> 00:08:57,890
 If the cost-effectiveness of the website is so low, what is the use of keeping it? 

97
00:08:57,890 --> 00:09:02,760
 Young man, having an idea and trying it out is a good thing. 

98
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:05,120
 How about this? I'm giving you one more chance. 

99
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:07,680
 - You can follow the original... 
 - No need. 

100
00:09:08,926 --> 00:09:10,716
 What did you say? 

101
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:17,647
 I said, I don't need it. 

102
00:09:17,647 --> 00:09:19,139
 I'm quitting. 

103
00:09:19,139 --> 00:09:21,010
 You're all about money. 

104
00:09:21,010 --> 00:09:23,230
 Doctor? 

105
00:09:23,230 --> 00:09:25,600
 Engineer? Technician? 

106
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:28,281
 To put it bluntly, you're just a capitalist. 

107
00:09:28,281 --> 00:09:30,600
 You are a wolf in sheep's clothing. 

108
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:32,960
 Zhou Ye, do you know what you're talking about? 

109
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:36,150
 Young man, I'd advise you to hold back your temper. 

110
00:09:36,150 --> 00:09:38,500
 Don't think too highly of yourself. 

111
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:40,300
 You're just nothing. 

112
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:46,450
 Calm down. 

113
00:09:51,790 --> 00:09:53,310
 I... 

114
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:56,450
 Let go! 

115
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,900
 You... Let me go! 

116
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:01,310
 I'll beat you to death! 

117
00:10:01,310 --> 00:10:04,600
 Come back here! 

118
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:09,820
Starting today, I'm the first person to straighten out the workplace.

119
00:10:09,820 --> 00:10:13,293
I'm the man Huan Dao can never have.

120
00:10:13,293 --> 00:10:14,760
I stand by you.

121
00:10:14,760 --> 00:10:16,090
Give me the box.

122
00:10:16,090 --> 00:10:17,590
This one?

123
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:20,670
What do you need this for?

124
00:10:20,670 --> 00:10:23,150
I'm leaving with you.

125
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:27,782
Actually, the boss doesn't necessarily want you to leave.

126
00:10:29,270 --> 00:10:31,820
It's me who can't stay any longer.

127
00:10:31,820 --> 00:10:35,582
After all, it's just that Huan Dao and I don't share the same philosophy.

128
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:44,690
Then I wish you both the best of luck in finding your own paths.

129
00:10:44,690 --> 00:10:46,480
Thank you, Fu Ying.

130
00:10:47,030 --> 00:10:50,471
Fu Ying, take good care of yourself.

131
00:10:56,930 --> 00:10:58,620
Pack up.

