- Senior Gao... 
 - What's the matter?

142
00:11:28,760 --> 00:11:32,070
Chen Huan Er, what's wrong?

143
00:11:33,430 --> 00:11:36,170
The data must be the old version.

144
00:11:36,170 --> 00:11:38,700
He must have opened the wrong file.

145
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:41,160
Even if you opened the wrong one,

146
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:45,100
can't you tell if your own experimental data is correct or not?

147
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:49,280
Tell me. How involved were you in this experiment?

148
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:50,580
I... Well...

149
00:11:50,580 --> 00:11:53,190
Chen Huan Er, tell me.

150
00:11:57,600 --> 00:12:02,580
Professor Qiu, the data was prepared by Tian Chi and I.

151
00:12:02,580 --> 00:12:04,670
Senior Gao Ang...

152
00:12:06,390 --> 00:12:08,580
usually just gives guidance.

153
00:12:08,580 --> 00:12:14,460
You can't even understand the basics, so how can you mentor your juniors?

154
00:12:14,460 --> 00:12:18,100
Get down. Chen Huan Er, present it.

155
00:12:18,100 --> 00:12:19,590
Yes.

156
00:12:26,220 --> 00:12:30,115
I'm sorry. Let me correct our experimental data for you.

157
00:12:31,430 --> 00:12:33,950
You have no idea how embarrassing it was today.

158
00:12:33,950 --> 00:12:36,800
So many people were in the hall.

159
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:41,500
Anyway, Gao Ang got what he deserved.

160
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:45,010
 That's good. I don't need to teach him a lesson for you. 

161
00:12:45,010 --> 00:12:47,580
Don't bother doing that for me.

162
00:12:47,580 --> 00:12:50,000
I can still handle it.

163
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:53,790
I'm going to have a feast today. I'm going to treat myself.

164
00:12:53,790 --> 00:12:55,248
 Can you add a pair of chopsticks? 

165
00:12:55,248 --> 00:12:57,560
Add a pair of chopsticks?

166
00:12:57,560 --> 00:12:58,760
What do you mean?

167
00:12:58,760 --> 00:13:00,493
 Look to the right. 

168
00:13:09,220 --> 00:13:11,590
Piggy Jing!

169
00:13:15,190 --> 00:13:16,740
Why are you here?

170
00:13:16,740 --> 00:13:19,150
Zhou Ye and I left Huan Dao together.

171
00:13:19,150 --> 00:13:21,500
From now on, we don't have to be separated anymore.

172
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:23,390
What do you mean?

173
00:13:23,390 --> 00:13:27,440
That means I'm now unemployed.

174
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:30,430
I'll have to rely on you to support me from now on.

175
00:13:30,430 --> 00:13:33,345
Okay. Then you have to be good to me from now on.

176
00:13:33,345 --> 00:13:34,690
No problem.

177
00:13:34,690 --> 00:13:37,800
Right, where are you staying tonight?

178
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:39,969
I'm still renting the same apartment as before.

179
00:13:39,969 --> 00:13:43,850
The owner never got around to renting it out, so I got it.

180
00:13:45,210 --> 00:13:46,360
Okay.

181
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:48,548
Wait here for me a while.

182
00:13:48,548 --> 00:13:50,220
Where are you going?

183
00:13:50,220 --> 00:13:52,566
I'll pack.

184
00:13:52,566 --> 00:13:54,270
What are you packing for?

185
00:13:54,270 --> 00:13:57,740
Why? Don't you want to live with me?

186
00:13:57,740 --> 00:13:59,499
Go now.

187
00:13:59,499 --> 00:14:00,770
- I'll wait for you here. 
 - Wait for me.

188
00:14:00,770 --> 00:14:02,070
Okay.

189
00:14:02,850 --> 00:14:04,730
Wait for me.

190
00:14:11,570 --> 00:14:14,190
We're back.

191
00:14:14,190 --> 00:14:16,130
We're back indeed.

192
00:14:17,220 --> 00:14:19,330
- It's pretty clean this time. 
 - Of course.

193
00:14:19,330 --> 00:14:21,515
Your little sheep slippers.

194
00:14:23,190 --> 00:14:25,220
Let me unpack your things.

195
00:14:25,220 --> 00:14:27,490
I can do it myself.

196
00:14:30,220 --> 00:14:35,120
Listen. During the day, I'll go to school, and you and Zhou Ye will work here.

197
00:14:35,120 --> 00:14:36,648
I need to get Zhou Ye a punch card machine.

198
00:14:36,648 --> 00:14:38,500
He likes slacking off.

199
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:40,310
He's very motivated now.

200
00:14:40,310 --> 00:14:41,880
He's determined to humiliate Huan Dao.

201
00:14:41,880 --> 00:14:43,960
Really?

202
00:14:46,340 --> 00:14:47,720
- Give it to me. 
 - You even bring this?

203
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:48,820
Don't look at it.

204
00:14:48,820 --> 00:14:52,170
You let me set it up in the dormitory, so I brought it all back.

205
00:14:52,170 --> 00:14:54,150
All right. Get me a glass of water.

206
00:14:54,150 --> 00:14:56,070
- Okay. 
 - Okay.

207
00:15:09,340 --> 00:15:11,700
 Why is the power out? 

208
00:15:12,880 --> 00:15:14,640
Don't be afraid. We have candles.

209
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:16,700
 I'll look for the candles and light them. 

210
00:15:16,700 --> 00:15:19,300
 Coming. The candles are lit. 

211
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:23,340
I'm coming in.

212
00:15:23,980 --> 00:15:25,990
Come... Come in.

213
00:15:33,390 --> 00:15:36,900
Well, I'll leave the candle here. I'm going out now.

214
00:15:36,900 --> 00:15:38,190
You...

215
00:15:38,190 --> 00:15:41,820
Can you stay for a bit?

216
00:15:41,820 --> 00:15:43,950
I'm scared.

217
00:15:45,010 --> 00:15:46,530
Okay.

218
00:16:07,550 --> 00:16:09,840
 Jing Xi Chi. 

219
00:16:10,980 --> 00:16:13,790
Jing Xi Chi.

220
00:16:13,790 --> 00:16:15,550
Yes?

221
00:16:15,550 --> 00:16:17,190
Nothing.

222
00:16:17,190 --> 00:16:22,300
I just want to say your name.

223
00:16:28,150 --> 00:16:31,190
Jing Xi Chi.

224
00:16:31,980 --> 00:16:33,950
Isn't "Xi" a polyphonic character?

225
00:16:33,950 --> 00:16:36,990
It can also be pronounced as "Qi."

226
00:16:38,670 --> 00:16:40,970
Qi Chi.

227
00:16:40,970 --> 00:16:45,190
I'm poor and drifting, and I've got to drink to drown my sorrows.

228
00:16:45,190 --> 00:16:49,670
Doesn't "Qi Chi" mean adrift?

229
00:16:51,030 --> 00:16:55,190
In addition to what you said, there's actually another saying.

230
00:16:55,190 --> 00:16:59,837
Under Heng Gate, you can have fun and rest.

231
00:16:59,837 --> 00:17:01,460
Have you ever heard of it?

232
00:17:01,460 --> 00:17:03,160
No.

233
00:17:03,980 --> 00:17:06,190
It's from the Classic of Poetry.

234
00:17:06,190 --> 00:17:09,190
It means that as long as your heart is calm,

235
00:17:09,190 --> 00:17:16,110
no matter how bad the situation is, you can use it as a shelter from the wind and rain.

236
00:17:17,010 --> 00:17:19,300
I see.

237
00:17:19,870 --> 00:17:25,910
Why does everyone call you Xi Chi instead of Qi Chi?

238
00:17:25,910 --> 00:17:30,760
When people see the word "Qi Chi," they think of adrift.

239
00:17:30,760 --> 00:17:36,260
My mom thought it was bad luck, so she said she'd call me Xi Chi instead.

240
00:17:36,260 --> 00:17:37,780
I got it.

241
00:17:37,780 --> 00:17:44,920
Aunt Lin wants you to be able to find a home wherever you go, right?

242
00:17:49,910 --> 00:17:51,840
So...

243
00:17:54,580 --> 00:17:56,937
Have you found it now?

244
00:18:07,590 --> 00:18:09,740
Jing Xi Chi.

245
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:15,730
We...

246
00:18:16,390 --> 00:18:18,770
we've taken such a long detour,

247
00:18:24,220 --> 00:18:26,100
But we made it back.

248
00:18:59,560 --> 00:19:01,220
They haven't arrived yet, have they?

249
00:19:01,220 --> 00:19:03,720
It's been a while.

250
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:06,180
Go over there and take a look.

251
00:19:06,180 --> 00:19:07,493
Year of the Monkey.

252
00:19:07,493 --> 00:19:10,990
- We have the same one. 
 - It hasn't changed much since we were here.

253
00:19:10,990 --> 00:19:14,010
- Huan Er. 
 - Huan Er, Jing Xi Chi.

254
00:19:14,010 --> 00:19:15,190
Fei Fan.

255
00:19:15,190 --> 00:19:16,560
- Fei Fan. 
